parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective valve stems can cause tire blowouts, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Valve stems break off at the tire rim
causing tires to go flat; tires shred or blow out at high speeds; valve stems leak air
causing tire pressure loss; tire walls are damaged due to defective valve stems.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure due to Poor Quality or Design
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Tires blow out at the sidewall; tread separates from the tire casing; tires shred or come apart; tires experience sudden loss of air pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Tire Manufacturers and Dealers to Address Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to address tire-related issues can lead to continued accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Tire manufacturers and dealers fail to replace defective valve stems or tires; dealers inspect tires but do not replace them; manufacturers blame consumers for tire failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Corrosion and Liner Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the fuel tank liner can cause the fuel system to become clogged, leading to stalling, loss of power, and engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or sputters while driving
water is present in the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel lines can cause fuel leaks, leading to engine fires, which can result in accidents or injuries.
The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spark plug failure can cause a sudden loss of power, hesitation, and stalling, which can lead to accidents, especially when hauling a load or driving on busy roads. The proximity of the fuel rail to the spark plugs also poses a risk of fuel leaks and fires.
Clutch failure can cause difficulty or inability to shift gears, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. The failure can also cause damage to the transmission and other components.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag failure can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust system issues can cause pollution, strong gases, and smoke, posing a risk to the environment and public health.
symptoms: Strong gases and smoke from the exhaust pipe.
